text: Masala Thosa soso, but sauces with it flavorless. The orange color sauce- see photo- was disgusting. Why serve something so bad when a good sauce is so easy to make?
Masala dosai is good. However, found the dahl to be slightly too salty. Creamy coconut chutney is delish!

Love the food of this stall, portion is big, staff are friendly. Also, they allowed ordering through WhatsApp.

The must-try are:-
1. Nasi Briyani with fried chicken
2. Rojak
3. Ikan Bilis Fried Rice
4. Roti Prata

Cannot find a better indian muslim stall than this.

Best service and have been a long-time customer for 4 years their egg prata and chicken curry are the best. Dont know why others give such bad ratings on their other foods. love the Prata thereüëçüëçüëç
Dosai was uncooked. Sambadam was like cooked plain dal. Coconut chutney was fine. Bad service. The cook offered to remake the dosai though.
